wiki.summary: “Praise the Lord (Da Shine)” is the fifth track from A$AP Rocky’s third studio album, TESTING. This song marks the third collaboration between Rocky and Skepta, following 2016’s “Put That on My Set” and 2017’s “Ghost Ride”. Prior to its release, the song was teased by both Rocky’s crew and Skepta during a since-expired Instagram live. The chorus and the last two verses interpolate DMX’s flow on “Who We Be,” paying homage to his legendary rhyming. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Praise the Lord (Da Shine)” is the fifth track from A$AP Rocky’s third studio album, TESTING. This song marks the third collaboration between Rocky and Skepta, following 2016’s “Put That on My Set” and 2017’s “Ghost Ride”. Prior to its release, the song was teased by both Rocky’s crew and Skepta during a since-expired Instagram live. The chorus and the last two verses interpolate DMX’s flow on “Who We Be,” paying homage to his legendary rhyming. Rocky released the music video for the song on June 5, 2018. The video was shot in Harlem and London, the respective birthplaces of the two emcees. The song features a prominent sample of “Andean Stroll Panpipe 02” from Apple GarageBand Jam Pack 5: World Music. Read more on Last.fm.
